The paper deals with object detection using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also addresses the issue of catastrophic forgetting, which is a problem in machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed solution involves a new loss function, which is a technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of multiple steps for incremental learning, which involves the use of neural networks and optimization algorithms (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents empirical analysis of the approach, which involves natural language processing techniques such as text analysis and data visualization (cs.CL).
